article.headline: IUPUI 80, Oral Roberts 75
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Brandon Cole and Maushae Byles each scored 20 points and IUPUI erased a nine-point second half deficit on its way to an 80-75 victory over Oral Roberts on Saturday. David Barlow hit the go-ahead 3-pointer with 4:12 to play to give the Jaguars a 66-64 lead and they never trailed after that. The Jaguars pushed their lead to 73-66 with 1:56 left, but Oral Roberts cut it to four with 22 seconds remaining. Free throws from Barlow and Brandon Cole in the final seconds sealed the game for IUPUI (17-7, 12-1). Caleb Green led Oral Roberts (15-10, 10-3) with a game-high 29 points. He grabbed six rebounds and had four assists. Larry Owens had the game's only double-double, scoring 11 points and pulling down 10 rebounds for Oral Roberts. Jonathan Bluitt scored 12. George Hill scored 15 points and had a game-high eight assists for IUPUI. Barlow finished with 12 points and six assists. The victory was IUPUI's eighth win in a row and pushes the Jaguars' lead over Oral Roberts to two games in the Mid-Continent Conference.
